<br>
By the way, what about the presumption of innocence.  A defendent is presumed innocent until the government prooves them guilty beyond reasonable doubt.  Maybe I'm one of the few who still believes in this.  And don't argue that you know all the evidence against him, we dont know what they have....its all classified.  Just because the government says thats the guy, he's guilty, doesnt make it so.  That's why we have courts. <p><br>
